<b>Active statuses to use:</b><br>
<ul>
    <li><b>BLOCKER</b> : Critical error preventing data submission (envelope release will not be possible).</li>
    <li><b>WARNING</b> : An issue has been detected that may be an error. No corrective action may be necessary in this case.</li>
    <li><b>OK</b> : No WARNING, ERROR or BLOCKER messages have been generated.</li>
    <li><b>INFO</b> : Informative message, often presenting summary statistics about the delivery.</li>
    <li><b>FAILED</b> : Script execution failed, e.g. due to memory problems or unresponsive third party web service.</li>
    <li><b>UNKNOWN</b> : This was used in older QA scripts (instead of FAILED or SKIPPED) and should be phased out.</li>
</ul>
<b>Deprecated statuses that will be phased out - please do not use these:</b><br>
<ul>
    <li><b>ERROR</b> : Non-critical error, but still requiring corrective action by the data reporter.</li>
    <li><b>SKIPPED</b> : There was "Nothing found to check", typically because of missing optional data elements.</li>
</ul>